<paragraph blockId="14.[140,1107,624,827]" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">
This species is known from northern 
<collectingRegion box="[555,699,624,651]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
and southern 
<collectingRegion box="[861,971,624,650]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">Colorado</collectingRegion>
. Individuals are colored similarly to 
<taxonomicName box="[402,555,659,685]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversale">
<emphasis box="[402,555,659,685]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">B. transversale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but are brighter and more reddish, and are more convex and shinier than other members of the group, with larger punctures in the elytral striae, and more convex intervals. While their color pattern is similar to members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[212,367,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversale">
<emphasis box="[212,367,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">B. transversale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, male genitalia and DNA sequences indicate a much closer relationship to 
<taxonomicName box="[311,469,801,826]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanum">
<emphasis box="[311,469,801,826]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">B. mexicanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1857" box="[525,638,800,826]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugubre">
<emphasis box="[525,638,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">B. lugubre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
